07/04/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- German Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer has expressed optimism about the future talks on Kosovo's final status, calling for negotiations in a "spirit of reconciliation" and active involvement by all parties concerned. Fischer's statement, quoted by German media Wednesday (6 April), came during a visit to Pristina. During talks with representatives of the Kosovo interim authorities and local Serb leaders, Fischer reiterated that the implementation of internationally set standards is a key condition for launching status discussions. (Die Welt - 07/04/05; Deutsche Welle, KosovaLive - 06/04/05)
